<chapter id="Position_Management">
  <title>Position Management</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=Account Services: Position Management;PERM=bg_access"
           id="PM" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Position Management</title>

    <para role="TEXT">The <emphasis role="bold">Position Management</emphasis>
    function allows the user to see a summary of balances for accounts they
    are authorised to use.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position Management - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">Position
      Management</emphasis> function, from the tool bar, select
      <emphasis>Account Services</emphasis> &gt; <emphasis>Position
      Management</emphasis>.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position Management Selection</title>

      <para role="TEXT">When <guisubmenu>Position Management</guisubmenu> is
      selected, the following menu items are displayed on the left hand side
      of the page provides a list of related functions that are available.
      This menu provides a number of functions as follows:</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><guimenuitem moreinfo="none">FX Account
            Activity</guimenuitem></term>

            <listitem>
              <para role="TEXT">Enables you to view the accounts and current balances for
              Foreign Exchange treasury transactions.</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><guimenuitem moreinfo="none">FX
            Positions</guimenuitem></term>

            <listitem>
              <para role="TEXT">Enables you to inquire about Foreign Exchange positions
              .</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist></para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position Management - FX Account Activity</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This section describes the forms in the <guimenu>FX
      Account Activity</guimenu> menu. You can use the FX Account Activity
      function to inquire about existing treasury transactions such as FX
      deals, wires and transfers, and certificate of deposits. The details are
      retrieved from the treasury back office.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">To view FX account activity details:</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT">Select <emphasis>Account Services &gt; Position Management
          &gt; FX Account Activity</emphasis> from the navigation menu. The
          Activity page appears.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT">In the <guilabel>Search Options</guilabel> section, complete
          the fields required for the filter, and then click
          <guibutton>Search</guibutton>.</para>

          <para role="TEXT">For more information about the search and display field
          descriptions, see the <emphasis>Account Activity
          Selection</emphasis> section.</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Account Activity Selection</title>

        <para role="TEXT">The valid filter/search criteria are as follows. To
        display all the records, enter an asterisk in any of the criteria
        fields.</para>

        <para role="TEXT"><informaltable role="TEXT">
            <tgroup cols="3">
              <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

              <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.0*" />

              <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="6.0*" />

              <thead>
                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Field</para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Type</para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Description</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>
              </thead>

              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Customer Reference</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <inlinemediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                          <imagedata fileref="../images/char_arrow.gif"
                                     width="2mm" />
                        </imageobject>
                      </inlinemediaobject>

                      <inlinemediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                          <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                     width="2mm" />
                        </imageobject>
                      </inlinemediaobject>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Mandatory. Reference provided by the customer for
                    the trade.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Start Date</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <inlinemediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                          <imagedata fileref="../images/char_arrow.gif"
                                     width="2mm" />
                        </imageobject>
                      </inlinemediaobject>

                      <inlinemediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                          <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                     width="2mm" />
                        </imageobject>
                      </inlinemediaobject>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Mandatory. Date the trade is entered. The account
                    activity details are retrieved from the <guilabel>Start
                    Date</guilabel>.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>  </informaltable></para>

            <para role="TEXT">When the required search/filter criteria have
            been entered, click the <guibutton>Search</guibutton> button to
            display a list of matching transactions. The columns displayed in
            the list are as follows:</para>
<para role="TEXT"><informaltable role="TEXT">
            <tgroup cols="2">
              <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

              <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

              <thead>
                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Field</para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Description</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>
              </thead>

              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Bank Ref</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Treasury Back Office reference number generated by
                    the back office for the FX trade request.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Description</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Details related to the trade or account
                    movement.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Post Date</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Date when the trade was entered.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Effective Date</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Value date or the settlement date of the
                    transaction.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Ccy</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Currency of the transaction.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Amount</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Amount of the transaction</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Instruction</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Status of the instruction attached to the trade. The
                    status is: </para>

                    <itemizedlist>
                      <listitem>
                        <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Incomplete</emphasis>, if the
                        instructions have not been added for both the payment
                        and receipt side of the trade.</para>
                      </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>

                    <itemizedlist>
                      <listitem>
                        <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Complete</emphasis>, if instructions
                        have been added for both the payment and receipt side
                        of the trade.</para>
                      </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>

                    <itemizedlist>
                      <listitem>
                        <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Awaiting Payment</emphasis>, if the
                        instruction is added only to the payment side of the
                        trade.</para>
                      </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>

                    <itemizedlist>
                      <listitem>
                        <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Awaiting Receipt</emphasis>, if the
                        instruction is added to the receipt side of the
                        trade.</para>
                      </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Maturity</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Maturity date of the deposit. This field is
                    applicable to the trade having deposit
                    transactions.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">
                      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Account</guilabel>
                    </para>
                  </entry>

                  <entry valign="top">
                    <para role="TEXT">Indicates the Call and Notice and Settlement account
                    movements. This field is applicable for wires and
                    transfers.</para>
                  </entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </informaltable></para>

        <para role="TEXT">The <guibutton>Download File</guibutton> button
        enables you to save the results in the PC. Click the
        <guibutton>Download File</guibutton> button and select one of the
        following options:</para>

        <itemizedlist role="TEXT">
          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT"><type>PDF</type> downloads the list to the PC as PDF
            file.</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT"><type>CSV</type> downloads the list to the PC as
            Comma-Separated Values file.</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

        <para role="TEXT">Use the <guilabel>PDF</guilabel> or
        <guilabel>CSV</guilabel> option to export the list as a report
        allowing it to be customized further for various office productivity
        tools. When the browser displays the <literal moreinfo="none">File
        Download</literal> prompt, save the file (default name is <filename
        moreinfo="none">pendingIP.xxx</filename>) or directly open it to
        launch <productname>Excel</productname> if it is available on the
        workstation.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position Management - FX Positions</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This section describes the forms in the <guimenu>FX
      Positions</guimenu> menu. </para>

      <para role="TEXT">To view FX Position details:</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT">Select <emphasis>Account Services &gt; Position Management
          &gt; FX Position</emphasis> from the navigation menu. The Position
          page appears.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT">In the <guilabel>Search Options</guilabel> section, complete
          the fields required for the filter, and then click
          <guibutton>Search</guibutton>.</para>

          <para role="TEXT">For more information about the search and display field
          descriptions, see the <emphasis>FX Positions Selection</emphasis>
          section.</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>

